# Mermaid Agent — Project Overview

AI-powered Mermaid diagram generator with live editing, auto-fix, and image enhancement.

## Architecture

- **Backend** (`backend/`): FastAPI + Pydantic AI agents powered by Google Gemini
- **Frontend** (`frontend/`): SvelteKit (Svelte 5 runes, Vite) with CodeMirror editor + Mermaid.js preview
- **Primary protocol**: WebSocket (`/api/chat/ws`) — server-side unified agent with client-side tools
- **Legacy REST**: `/api/chat`, `/api/fix`, `/api/chat/image`, `/api/enhance` endpoints still exist for backward compat
- **Proxy**: Frontend `routes/api/[...path]/+server.ts` has been removed. Nginx handles routing in Docker; Vite proxy handles dev.
- **Docker**: `docker-compose.yml` runs three services: `nginx` (exposed on :3000), `frontend` (internal), `backend` (internal)

## Key Data Flow

```
WebSocket flow (primary):
User chat → WS /api/chat/ws → unified_agent (Gemini)
  ← tool_request: render_and_capture(code) → frontend renders + captures screenshot
  → tool_result: {image: base64} or {error: msg}
  (agent fixes code and retries if error)
  ← tool_request: capture_screenshot → frontend captures current diagram
  → calls enhance_diagram tool (Gemini image gen)
  ← enhanced_image, message, done

Legacy REST (backward compat):
POST /api/chat → mermaid_agent → mermaid_code + explanation
POST /api/fix  → fix_agent     → corrected code
POST /api/chat/image → convert_agent → code from image
POST /api/enhance → enhance_image   → enhanced PNG or null
```

## Deployment

- **nginx** reverse proxy is the sole exposed service (port 3000 → nginx port 80)
- `location /api/chat/ws` → backend (WebSocket upgrade headers)
- `location /api/` → backend (REST)
- `location /` → frontend (SvelteKit)
- Backend and frontend are internal-only (no ports exposed to host)

## Backend Key Files

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `app/main.py` | WebSocket endpoint `/api/chat/ws` + legacy REST routes |
| `app/schema.py` | Request/response Pydantic models (`ChatRequest`, `ChatResponse`, etc.) |
| `app/services/agent.py` | `AgentDeps` (WS tool bridge), `unified_agent` with 4 tools, legacy agents for REST |
| `app/services/prompts.py` | System prompts: `SYSTEM_PROMPT` (unified), `LEGACY_SYSTEM_PROMPT`, `FIX_PROMPT`, etc. |
| `app/services/doc_fetcher.py` | Fetches Mermaid syntax docs from GitHub into `app/docs/` at startup |
| `app/docs/` | Cached Mermaid syntax `.md` files + `config.schema.json` (gitignored, fetched at runtime) |

## Frontend Key Files

| File | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `src/lib/ws.ts` | WebSocket client: sends messages, dispatches events, executes client-side tools |
| `src/lib/chat.svelte.ts` | Central store (`createChatStore`): all state via `$state` runes — messages, diagramCode, chartType, enhancedImage |
| `src/lib/ChatPanel.svelte` | Chat UI: message list, Chart Type dropdown, text input, image upload |
| `src/lib/Editor.svelte` | CodeMirror 6 editor with `codemirror-lang-mermaid`, fires `onFocus` callback |
| `src/lib/Preview.svelte` | Full-width tab bar (Mermaid / AI Enhanced), rendering, SVG→JPEG capture, zoom/pan |
| `src/lib/types.ts` | `Message` interface |
| `src/routes/+page.svelte` | Main page: 3-panel resizable layout, wires store to components |

## Important Patterns

- **Svelte 5 runes**: All state uses `$state()`, `$effect()`, `$props()` — no legacy `$:` or stores
- **Unified agent loop**: Server runs one `pydantic-ai` agent with 4 tools. Client-side tools (`render_and_capture`, `capture_screenshot`) execute via WS tool_request/tool_result protocol. Auto-fix is handled by the agent (it sees render errors and retries).
- **AgentDeps**: Dataclass injected via `RunContext[AgentDeps]`. Contains the WebSocket + pending tool futures. `request_client_tool()` sends a WS message and awaits the response via `asyncio.Future`.
- **Tab content persistence**: Preview uses `style:display` (not `{#if}`) so both Mermaid SVG and Enhanced panels stay in DOM
- **Editor focus → Mermaid tab**: Clicking/focusing the code editor automatically switches the preview to the Mermaid tab
- **Agent tools**: `read_mermaid_syntax`, `read_mermaid_config` (server-side docs), `render_and_capture` (client-side), `enhance_diagram` (server-side image gen)
- **No Enhance button**: Enhancement is triggered by the agent when appropriate (user asks via chat). No manual Enhance button in the UI.

## Tests

- **Backend**: `pytest` — `backend/tests/test_api.py` (REST + WebSocket endpoints), `test_agent.py` (tool functions). Run: `cd backend && uv run pytest`
- **Frontend**: Playwright e2e — `frontend/test/e2e.spec.ts`. Run: `cd frontend && npx playwright test`
- **WSL2 note**: E2E tests block Google Fonts (`blockExternalRequests`) and wait for `[data-hydrated]` to handle SSR hydration timing.

## Environment

- `backend/.env`: `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_MODEL` (default gemini-2.5-flash), `ENHANCE_MODEL` (default gemini-2.5-flash-preview-04-17)
- No `python` binary in WSL2 — use `uv run python` or `python3`
